  "riddle": "1. Unearth the height of a New Zealander who has taken the field in league football. Now turn to the article linked prominently under \"Article.\"\n\n2. Contemplate your last result: What prime number steps next after that height?\n\n3. There is a place in the southern hemisphere where governmental decisions are decreed amidst the ocean's cradle. Determine the elevation at this capital city known for its bustling wind.\n\n4. A city famed for its wine and listed among treasured heritages — in what century did it earn such distinction? Seek those indigenous to a whole hemisphere.\n\n5. Track down a page that introduces those who first called two continents home. How many major divisions does its table of contents display?\n\n6. Should you place your feet where these original inhabitants are remembered, what elevation would your shoes rest upon?\n\n7. Seek discovery in a digital atlas: How do modern wanderers rate this same ancestral region?\n\n8. Gather your findings from clues 6 and 7, then calculate the distance their numbers span by taking the absolute difference.\n\n9. The land of liberty set the stage for this riddle's next morsel. What is the grand size, measured in square kilometers, of a nation famed for Eiffel and patisseries?\n\n10. With shores caressed by three continents, size the vast expanse of this sea that birthed so many civilizations.\n\n11. Your previous answer, when viewed in digital form, flares up in lights: How plentiful are the ones within its binary blaze?\n\n12. As a destination of wisdom, a capital city at the heart of the Pharaoh’s domain awaits you. Ascertain this ancient land's altitude.\n\n13. Discover when the treasure trove of American research was established, where congress' knowledge gathers dust no more.\n\n14. To conclude, take the numbers from clues 1, 2, and 7. Their synergy leads to simplicity via a classic ancient numeral trick — compute their digital root to unlock the final digit.",
